missionEventData.data2: In the far reaches of the Outer Rim a rebellion is forming. A rebel cell led by the frigate Redemption and ace pilot Keyan Farlander have been striking back against the evil galactic empire. But the Emperor is at the height of his power, and even now he is marshalling his forces at the edge of the mid-rim. But help has come from the most unlikely of places. The captain of an imperial corvette has sent the rebel freedom fighters a secret message, he wishes to defect...

missionEventData.data1: For the price of a few drinks in one of the sector's less respectable establishments Rebel Intelligence has been able to secure the location of our lost pilots. A convoy of Imperial Shuttles are conveying the prisoners through a little used system on the edge of the mid-rim. Your mission goals are simple. Disable the Prisoner Transports using your ion cannons, and provide cover for our rescue operation. If this goes to plan we will be able to reverse the damage done by the Ars Opus.
Red Squadron head to the jump point immediately. The rescue transports will follow.
Acknowledged Redemption. We're on our way.
Red One to Command. Transports ready for boarding.
Acknowledged Red One. Dagger One and Two commencing jump.
Dagger One commencing docking with transport Lambda.
Dagger Two commencing docking with transport Omicron.
This is Dagger One. Transfer for tech staff complete. Disengaging.
This is Dagger Two. Transfer for tech staff complete. Pushing off,.
Dagger One moving to jump point.
Dagger Two moving to jump point.
The Harasser just dropped in and she's launching Ties. Keep them of the Rescue transports.
Activate Ion Cannons and disable those transports!
Wait! Four Imperial transports exiting Hyperspace.
We've got what we came for. Let's get out of here before they launch more Ties.

missionEventData.data3: Our rescue operation turned up a surprise. Not only were we able to liberate our lost pilots, amidst the assorted outer rim riffraff we discovered several key members of the Sullustan cabinet. This could be the beginning of a new opportunity…
